---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NoteBox from '../components/NoteBox.astro';
import { catalog } from '../lib/data.mjs';

const gameCount = catalog().length;
---
<Layout
  title="About GamePriceMap — data sources, update cadence & policies"
  description="How GamePriceMap works: where the price data comes from, how often it updates, how it is validated, and what we will never list."
>
  <div class="page-head wrap">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span>/</span>About</div>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>GamePriceMap tracks game prices across Steam and the Nintendo eShop — regional pricing, current deals, historical lows and free games — for {gameCount} games and growing.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="wrap" style="padding-bottom: 32px; max-width: 860px;">
    <section class="section" style="padding-top: 8px;">
      <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-pixel); font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 12px;">Where the data comes from</h2>
      <table class="region-full">
        <thead><tr><th>Data</th><th>Source</th><th>Updates</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td style="font-weight:800;">Steam regional prices</td><td>Steam storefront (18 regions)</td><td class="mono">daily</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="font-weight:800;">eShop regional prices</td><td>Nintendo storefront price service (16 regions)</td><td class="mono">daily</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="font-weight:800;">Multi-store PC deals</td><td>CheapShark (Steam, GOG, Fanatical, GMG, Humble …)</td><td class="mono">daily</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="font-weight:800;">Historical lows</td><td>CheapShark records + Nintendo eShop index + our own tracking since Jul 2026</td><td class="mono">daily</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="font-weight:800;">Free games</td><td>Epic Games Store promotions + Steam 100% discounts</td><td class="mono">daily</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="font-weight:800;">Release calendar</td><td>Nintendo eShop listings + Steam coming-soon</td><td class="mono">weekly</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="font-weight:800;">Exchange rates</td><td>ExchangeRate-API (USD base)</td><td class="mono">daily</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p style="color: var(--text-2); font-weight: 600; margin-top: 12px;">
        Every refresh passes a validation gate before it is published: prices must be positive,
        discounts in range, currency conversions within tolerance and region coverage stable.
        When a source is unreachable we keep the last good data and say so on the
        <a href="/status" style="font-weight:800; color: var(--red);">status page</a> —
        a stale number is never silently replaced with a wrong one.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-pixel); font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 12px;">What we will and won't do</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--text-2); font-weight: 600;">
        We only list verified, authorized storefronts — no gray-market key resellers.
        Rankings are always ordered by price, never by commission.
        All-time lows are labeled with their provenance: externally recorded lows say so,
        and prices we observed ourselves say "lowest since we started tracking".
        Giveaway records are not treated as purchase prices.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-pixel); font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 12px;">Fair warnings</h2>
      <NoteBox>
        Regional prices are store list prices converted at daily exchange rates —
        not checkout totals. Taxes, payment fees and rounding differ by country,
        and whether you can buy from another region depends on your account,
        payment method and platform rules. Prices refresh daily, so a flash sale
        can briefly show its previous state.
      </NoteBox>
      <p style="color: var(--text-3); font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 12px;">
        GamePriceMap is an independent project, not affiliated with Valve, Nintendo,
        Epic Games or any listed store. Game artwork and names belong to their publishers.
        Multi-store deal data by CheapShark; exchange rates by ExchangeRate-API.
        Contact: <span class="mono">yiyi22331999@gmail.com</span>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
